{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Dick Boer | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1957|8|31|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Axel, Netherlands|Axel]], Netherlands<ref>Hans Reichart, [http://www.mt.nl/479/76194/mt500-van-2015/het-succesverhaal-van-dick-boer-ahold.html Het sucessverhaal van Dick Boer] in ''Management Team'', 29 April 2013 {{nl}}</ref> | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | nationality = Dutch | ethnicity = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = Businessman | years_active = | salary = €2,533,000 (total compensation, 2014)<ref name=Bloomberg /> | net_worth = | title = Former CEO, [[Ahold Delhaize]] | term = 2011-July 2018 | predecessor = [[John Rishton]] | successor = [[Frans Muller]] | parents = | spouse = | children = }}
'''Dick Boer''' (born 31 August 1957) is a Dutch businessman, and the president and chief executive officer (CEO) of [[Ahold Delhaize]], the supermarket chain from 2011 to 2018.
==Early life== Boer was born on 31 August 1957.<ref name=Ahold>{{cite web|title=Dick Boer |url=https://www.ahold.com/Corporate-governance/Executive-Committee-and-Management-Board/Dick-Boer.htm |website=Ahold |accessdate=26 June 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627035911/https://www.ahold.com/Corporate-governance/Executive-Committee-and-Management-Board/Dick-Boer.htm |archivedate=27 June 2015 |df= }}</ref>
==Career== Boer joined Ahold in 1998, rising to CEO on 1 March 2011,<ref name=Bloomberg>{{cite web|title=Executive Profile: Dick Boer|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=12826393&ticker=AH:NA|website=Bloomberg|accessdate=26 June 2015}}</ref> succeeding [[John Rishton]].<ref name=FoodWorld>{{cite web|title=Ahold Announces Executive Changes: Dick Boer To Be Ahold CEO, Carl Schlicker To Become Ahold USA COO|url=http://best-met.com/news/ahold-announces-leadership-changes-dick-boer-ceo-ahold-carl-schlicker-coo-us/|website=Food World|accessdate=26 June 2015}}</ref>
On 24 June 2015, when Ahold and [[Delhaize]] announced that they were to combine their businesses as [[Ahold Delhaize]], it was stated that Boer would become CEO of the merged company, with [[Frans Muller]], CEO of Delhaize to become deputy CEO and chief integration officer. <ref name=SupermarketNews>{{cite news|title=Ahold, Delhaize complete merger agreement|url=http://supermarketnews.com/ahold-delhaize-merger/ahold-delhaize-complete-merger-agreement|accessdate=26 June 2015|work=SupermarketNews|date=24 June 2015}}</ref>
In July 2018, Boer retired and was succeeded by his deputy, [[Frans Muller]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2018/04/05/1465425/0/en/Ahold-Delhaize-CEO-Dick-Boer-retires-Frans-Muller-appointed-as-successor-effective-July-1-2018.html|title=Ahold Delhaize CEO Dick Boer retires; Frans Muller appointed as successor effective July 1, 2018|first=Ahold|last=Delhaize|publisher=|accessdate=8 July 2018}}</ref>
==Other roles== Boer is a board member of the [[Consumer Goods Forum]]. He is vice-chair of the executive board of The [[Confederation of Netherlands Industry and Employers]] (VNO-NCW). He is a member of the advisory board of [[G-Star Raw]].<ref name=Ahold /> He also has three roles at the [[World Economic Forum]] 2017: governor of the consumer industries community, steward of the future of health and healthcare system, and co-chair of the human centric health steering committee.{{citation needed|date=January 2017}}
