'''Expert-as-a-Service''' (ExaaS) is an online delivery model of human [[consulting]] and/or automated [[knowledge transfer]]. Similarly to SaaS ([[Software as a service]]) the concept of ExaaS comes from the remote nature of processing data and/or providing service. The user of ExaaS <ref>{{cite web|last=Thiede |first=Charles |url=http://www.business2community.com/strategy/3-reasons-experts-service-future-consulting-0917775#frvhQ38cJBmi6lHV.97 |title=3 Reasons Why Experts-as-a-Service is the Future of Consulting |publisher=Business2community.com |date=2014-06-17 |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref> accesses the service through a [[webpage]], [[VoiP]], [[Instant messaging|IM]], etc. or any related [[mobile app]]. Typical ExaaS providers are [[consultants]], [[lawyers]], [[Physician|physicians]], [[teachers]] etc. 
Biztech Magazine claims that  "...Everything as a service...Clouding Will Disrupt the World..."<ref>{{cite web|last=Etwaru |first=Richie |url=http://www.biztechmagazine.com/article/2013/02/everything-service-how-clouding-will-disrupt-world |title=Everything as a Service: How Clouding Will Disrupt the World — BizTech |publisher=Biztechmagazine.com |date=2013-02-21 |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref> and according to Business2Customers magazine there are "...3 Reasons Why Experts-as-a-Service is the Future of Consulting..."<ref>{{cite web|last=Thiede |first=Charles |url=http://www.business2community.com/strategy/3-reasons-experts-service-future-consulting-0917775#mrhk0oV6t6rVos8S.97 |title=3 Reasons Why Experts-as-a-Service is the Future of Consulting |publisher=Business2community.com |date=2014-06-17 |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref>

ExaaS is the general term for newer consulting or expertise based [[online services]] like CaaS (Consulting-as-a-Service) or JaaS (Justice-as-a-Service) <ref name="henrikzillmer1">{{cite web|url=http://henrikzillmer.com/justice-as-a-service |title=Justice-as-a-Service |publisher=Henrik Zillmer |date= |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref>

CaaS companies or individuals deliver online consulting services (The Consulting-as-a-Service model (CONaaS) by Luke Marson,<ref>{{cite web|last=Marson |first=Luke |url=https://lukemarson.wordpress.com/2013/09/03/the-consulting-as-a-service-model-conaas/ |title=The Consulting-as-a-Service model (CONaaS) &#124; Luke Marson |publisher=Lukemarson.wordpress.com |date= |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref> sales diagnostics by Miklos Kadar,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mikloskadar.com/ |title=ExaaS |publisher=Miklos Kadar |date= |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref> 
Introducing Executive As A Service by GconnTec <ref>{{cite web|url=http://gconntec.com/exaas-value-proposition/ |title=EXaaS – Value Proposition |publisher=GconnTec |date= |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref>)

According to BusinessInsider JaaS companies "...Find You Money You Didn't Know You Were Owed..." <ref>{{cite web|author=Tech |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/airhelp-and-fixed-help-you-fight-airlines-and-parking-tickets-2014-7 |title=Airhelp and Fixed help you fight airlines and parking tickets |publisher=Business Insider |date=2014-07-25 |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref> by providing legal or consumer rights services. And according to Henrik Zillmer "...There’s a new wave of customer empowerment coming..." <ref name="henrikzillmer1"/>  
He lists honourable mentions of JaaS services like Paribus,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://paribus.co/|title=Paribus.co|author=Paribus Co|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Paribus.co|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref> Airhelp,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.getairhelp.com/en |title=AirHelp - Get compensation from delayed flights! |publisher=Getairhelp.com |date= |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref> Fixed,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fixed.com/ |title=Get your ticket and point dismissed |publisher=Fixed |date= |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref> [[BillFixers]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billfixers.com/|title=BillFixers - We Negotiate Lower Bills For You|work=BillFixers|accessdate=31 March 2016}}</ref> 71lbs <ref>{{cite web|author=Jose Li |url=https://www.71lbs.com/ |title=71 Pounds &#124; FedEx & UPS Shipping Refunds for Late Deliveries |publisher=71lbs.com |date=2016-03-16 |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref>)

