{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}} The '''Global Peter Drucker Forum''' is an international management conference dedicated to the management philosophy of [[Peter Drucker]]. Drucker, who lived from 1909 to 2005, was a management professor, writer, and consultant, frequently referred to as a "management guru." The Forum is held annually in November, in Drucker's home town of [[Vienna]], Austria and is put on by the Peter Drucker Society Europe, an affiliate of the [http://www.druckerinstitute.com Drucker Institute] at [[Claremont Graduate University]].
==Editions== The first Global Peter Drucker Forum was held on November 19, 2009, marking what would have been the 100th birthday of the late Peter Drucker.<ref name=people&strategy /> The forum included presentations by management philosopher and author [[Charles Handy]], [[Kellogg School of Management]] professor [[Philip Kotler]], economist [[Peter Lorange]], economist and consultant [[Fredmund Malik]], [[C.K. Prahalad]] of the [[Stephen M. Ross School of Business]] and [[Simon-Kucher & Partners]] chairman [[Hermann Simon]].<ref name=people&strategy>{{cite journal|title=HRPS, People & Strategy Attend First Global Drucker Forum|journal=People & Strategy|year=2009|url=http://drucker-ws.org/pdf/HRPS_PSIssue32%204_Final.pdf#page=69|accessdate=12 September 2011}}</ref>
Drucker's widow, Doris, supported the forum prior to her death in 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/42878e2c-c879-11e7-ab18-7a9fb7d6163e|title=A beginner’s guide to the Drucker Forum|last=Hill|first=Andrew|date=15 November 2017|website=Financial Times|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2 December 2018|registration=yes}}</ref> {| class="wikitable" |+ !Year !Dates !Theme !Venue |- |2009 |19–20 November<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://druckersociety.at/index.php/day-1-19-november-2009/|title=Program 2009|last=|first=|date=|website=Drucker Society|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2 December 2018}}</ref> | |Haus der Industrie |- |2010 |18–19 November<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://druckersociety.at/index.php/pdf-2010/program|title=Program 2010|last=|first=|date=|website=Drucker Society|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2 December 2018}}</ref> | |[[Stadtpalais Liechtenstein|Liechtenstein Palace]] |- |2011 |3–4 November |A Quest for Legitimacy: How Managers Can Shape the Future |[[Vienna University]] |- |2012 |15–16 November |Capitalism 2.0: New Horizons for Managers |Aula der Wissenschaften |- |2013 | |Managing Complexity<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.druckersociety.at/index.php|title=News|last=|first=|date=|website=Drucker Society|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2 December 2018}}</ref> | |- |2014 | |The Great Transformation – Managing Our Way to Prosperity<ref name=":0" /> | |- |2015 | |Claiming Our Humanity – Managing in the Digital Age<ref name=":0" /> | |- |2016 | |The Entrepreneurial Society – Moving Beyond a Society of Employees<ref name=":0" /> | |- |2017 |16–17 November |Growth & Inclusive Prosperity – The Secular Management Challenge<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.druckersociety.at/index.php|title=Home|last=|first=|date=|website=Drucker Society|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2 December 2018}}</ref> | |- |2018 |29–30 November |Management: The Human Dimension<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.druckerforum.org/home/|title=10th Global Peter Drucker Forum|last=|first=|date=|website=www.druckerforum.org|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2 December 2018}}</ref> |[[Hofburg]] |}
==Peter Drucker Challenge== The Peter Drucker Challenge was added to the Forum in 2010. The challenge is an essay competition open to you business leaders. The topic of the challenge changes annually but is related to the works of Peter Drucker.<ref name=druckerchallenge>{{cite web|title=The 2011 Peter Drucker Challenge|url=http://www.druckerchallenge.org/|work=Peter Drucker Challenge|accessdate=12 September 2011}}</ref>
===2011 Challenge=== The 2011 Peter Drucker Challenge focused on the topic of, "management, what is it good for?". The competition closed in August and the winners were announced by Peter Drucker Society Europe. Jury was composed of Deepa Prahalad, John Peters and Elizabeth Haas Edersheim.
===2010 Challenge=== The 2010 Peter Drucker Challenge received 214 entries.<ref name="AMDISA">{{cite web|url=http://www.amdisa.org/efmd.html|title=EFMD Announces 2nd Global Peter Drucker Management Forum18th to 19th November, 2010at Vienna, Austria|work=AMDISA|accessdate=12 September 2011}}</ref> The competition was judged by [[Danica Purg]], who was named "Dean of the year" by the Academy for International Business, chief executive for [[Emerald Group Publishing]] John Peters and author Elizabeth Haas-Edersheim. The judges selected 12 top essayists, with first place going to Florian Ramseger.<ref name=emerald>{{cite web|title=Summaries of the top 12 Essays|url=http://www.emeraldinsight.com/drucker/pdf/essay_summaries.pdf?PHPSESSID=so508n15chp861qrrjec5r3ca0|work=The Peter Drucker Essay Challenge|publisher=Emerald Insights|accessdate=12 September 2011}}</ref><ref name=businessweek>{{cite news|last=Wartzman|first=Rick|title=Cloud Computing and Peter Drucker|url=http://www.businessweek.com/managing/content/dec2010/ca2010123_832440.htm|accessdate=12 September 2011|newspaper=Business Week}}</ref>
